    public abstract class ExpectedRangeQuery
extends FitnessFilterQuery
    Additional layer of abstraction for a query that deals with expected ranges for a variety of metrics.

      • getSpeedRangeValueMap

        @NonNull
protected com.intel.ndg.sdi.cap.common.ValueMap getSpeedRangeValueMap(@NonNull
                                                                               android.content.Context context,
                                                                               @NonNull
                                                                               CUIResultBundle<nz.co.pltech.arda.core.api.Range> rangeBundle,
                                                                               @NonNull
                                                                               com.intel.ndg.sdi.cap.dlg.common.utils.UnitSystem unitSystem)
        Generates a value map containing information for a given speed range. If the given bundle contains a valid range, the value map will contain the following information: QueryResultKey.METRIC: Code for the metric. QueryResultKey.MIN: Lower bound for the range. QueryResultKey.MAX: Upper bound for the range. QueryResultKey.UNIT: Unit in which the result is given. QueryResultKey.RESULT_CODE: Code indicating the correct completion of the value map or indicating a specific condition that occurred while gathering all the information.
        Parameters:
        rangeBundle - A bundle potentially containing a range for the metric.
        Returns:
        A non-null value map containing the information described above.

      • getPaceRangeValueMap

        @NonNull
protected com.intel.ndg.sdi.cap.common.ValueMap getPaceRangeValueMap(@NonNull
                                                                              android.content.Context context,
                                                                              @NonNull
                                                                              CUIResultBundle<nz.co.pltech.arda.core.api.Range> rangeBundle,
                                                                              @NonNull
                                                                              com.intel.ndg.sdi.cap.dlg.common.utils.UnitSystem unitSystem)
        Generates a value map containing information for a given pace range. If the given bundle contains a valid range, the value map will contain the following information: QueryResultKey.METRIC: Code for the metric. QueryResultKey.MIN: Lower bound for the range. QueryResultKey.MAX: Upper bound for the range. QueryResultKey.UNIT: Unit in which the result is given. QueryResultKey.RESULT_CODE: Code indicating the correct completion of the value map or indicating a specific condition that occurred while gathering all the information. IMPORTANT: This method assumes pace range is given in MinutesPerKilometer, as provided by ARDA.
        Parameters:
        rangeBundle - A bundle potentially containing a range for the metric.
        unitSystem - Unit system such that the appropriate round heuristic is applied for the metric.
        Returns:
        A non-null value map containing the information described above.

      • getPaceRangeValueMapFromSpeed

        @NonNull
protected com.intel.ndg.sdi.cap.common.ValueMap getPaceRangeValueMapFromSpeed(@NonNull
                                                                                       android.content.Context context,
                                                                                       @NonNull
                                                                                       CUIResultBundle<nz.co.pltech.arda.core.api.Range> speedRangeBundle,
                                                                                       @NonNull
                                                                                       com.intel.ndg.sdi.cap.dlg.common.utils.UnitSystem unitSystem)
        Generates a value map containing information for a given pace range. In this particular variant, the method will convert a speed range to the appropriate pace range and then resort to getPaceRangeValueMap(Context, CUIResultBundle, UnitSystem). If the given bundle contains a valid range, the value map will contain the following information: QueryResultKey.METRIC: Code for the metric. QueryResultKey.MIN: Lower bound for the range. QueryResultKey.MAX: Upper bound for the range. QueryResultKey.UNIT: Unit in which the result is given. QueryResultKey.RESULT_CODE: Code indicating the correct completion of the value map or indicating a specific condition that occurred while gathering all the information. IMPORTANT: This method assumes pace range is given in MinutesPerKilometer, as provided by ARDA.
        Parameters:
        speedRangeBundle - A bundle potentially containing a speed range to be converted to pace.
        unitSystem - Unit system such that the appropriate round heuristic is applied for the metric.
        Returns:
        A non-null value map containing the information described above.
